The New Global Politics of the Asia-Pacific, 2nd edition

Routledge: New York and London. 274pp. + x.

Michael Connors, Associate Professor of Political Science, University of Nottingham, Malaysia.

Remy Davison, Jean Monnet Chair in Politics & Economics, Monash University, Australia.

Joern Dosch, Professor of Asian Studies, Rostok University, Germany.

© 2012 Michael K. Connors, Remy Davison and Joern Dosch

The new, fully updated second edition of The New Global Politics of the Asia Pacific builds on its coherent framework for understanding the complex international and global politics of the Asia Pacific. 

Key content includes:

        the US in the Asia Pacific;

        China and Japan in the Asia Pacific;

        Southeast Asia in the Asia Pacific;

        India in the Asia Pacific;

        Russia in the Asia Pacific;

        Australia in the Asia Pacific;

        Europe in the Asia Pacific;

        globalization, regionalism and political economy;

        Asian values, democracy and human rights;

        transnational actors;

        region security order and the impact of terrorism on the region.

A highly topical account, which provides an overview of the main actors, institutions and contemporary issues such as security, terrorism and transnational actors, the book is required reading for students of Asian studies, international politics, and anyone interested in the region.
